<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100210462753266></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100210462753266><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=6140&mid=100210462753266>RE: I have some for sale</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84649><span id=Scholar>Troodon</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>51 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 3rd 6:23 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Note that these aren't the only cheap 10 slot containers you can buy anymore.  If you go to the gnome pirate outpost in Iceclad Ocean, you can buy deluxe toolboxes for about 1 1/2pp each.  They are 10 slot containers, weigh 3.5, no weight reduction, and can hold giant or smaller items.  Obviously this is a crappy container for lugging things around in, unless you really had no other container with a giant capacity, but they're excellent to keep in the bank for storing items.  These items can also be used with gnomes' tinkering skill.<br><br>No point in paying the rediculous prices deluxe sewing kits go for anymore.  They now only exist in the hands of players who owned a large sewing kit before the patch changed them to deluxe sewing kits.  Merchants don't sell them anymore, and any that were sold to merchants were instantly destroyed.  If you want to make a tailored item with more than 8 ingredients, you have to find a community loom if you don't happen to have a deluxe sewing kit.<br>&nbsp;<br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu, Level 32 Iksar Monk, Jaggedpine Defender, Solusek Ro</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99987353119623></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99987353119623><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=6140&mid=99987353119623>a bit of history</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=651><span id=Sage>Verdandi</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>41 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 7th 10:38 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.91]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Way back at the dawn of time, two kinds of tailoring kits were available from vendors: large (8 slots) and small (2 slots).  Then, when cultural tailoring (for halflings, erudites, and wood elves) was added, new kits (10 slots) were introduced that could only be used by those two races to make their cultural armors.  When Velious came out, another kit was made available from stores in Velious cities, the coldain tanning kit (8 slots) that must be used to make the Velious tailored armors.  <br><br>Then, because they were about to introduce old world armor that had more than 8 ingredients, the old world original large kits were increased to have 10 slots.  But then, people started complaining more loudly because this change meant that the large tailoring kits had as many slots as tailored backpacks but weighed less and held bigger items.  So, the Powers That Be decided to remove the 10 slot tailoring kits from vendors.  The problem was that they couldn't simply change them back to 8 slots, because that would cause problems for people who had items in all 10 slots.  So, they changed the existing 10-slot large kits into a new item, Deluxe kits, and changed vendors back to the original large kits with only 8 slots.  <br><br>Therefore, the only deluxe tailoring kits in existance are ones that players had in their possession when these changes were made.  If you find them on a vendor, it is because someone sold it to that vendor.  For those who need 10 slots for the recipes with more than 8 ingredients (Wu's Fighting armor), they also added Looms to some cities.  Looms are stationary containers that you go to in a city and use on the spot, like ovens or brew barrels or forges. <br><br>(Credit goes to Oakwood Moonblaze and Schmoozo Gladhand for their post here:) <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornertailoring.showMessage?topicID=2666.topic" target=_new>http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornertailoring.showMessage?topicID=2666.topic</a><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
